---
import Exercise from "@/components/Articles/Exercise/Exercise.astro";
import Keyword from "@/components/Articles/Keyword.astro";
import ExerciseSnippet from "@/components/Articles/Exercise/ExerciseSnippet.astro";
import ExternalLink from "@/components/Articles/ExternalLink.astro";
---

<Exercise exercise={1} title="Identifing Redis Tokens">
  <p>
    Using what you have learned in this chapter, define in your own code all the
    <Keyword word="TokenKinds" /> you can identify from the following commands:
  </p>

  <ExerciseSnippet
    code={`SET author Alejandro
GETEX author EX 20
EXISTS author
SET articleRewrites 3
INCRBY articleRewrites 1
INCR articleRewrites`}
  />

  <p>
    Notice that the commands above are <strong>not random</strong> — they were chosen
    to cover every distinct <Keyword word="TokenKind" /> our <Keyword
      word="Lexer"
    /> will need to recognize. Take your time before moving on.
  </p>

  <p>
    💡 <strong>Want to check your work?</strong> Compare your solution against the
    <ExternalLink
      href="https://github.com/dyxgou/redis/blob/a2c128bd7000104b1f9bb3ecb2a7fcb7b4c4b8d4/pkg/token/token.go#L15"
      text="pkg/token/token.go"
    /> file in the source code.
  </p>
  <p>
    Have questions or want to share your solution? Reach out on <ExternalLink
      href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/diego-alejandro-417357219/"
      text="LinkedIn"
    /> — I'd love to see what you come up with.
  </p>
</Exercise>
